	<h3>Page Links (2)</h3>
	
	Look at the URL of this page. It is the request from the PageLink. We call this simple form of request a <strong>render request</strong>.<br/>
	When Tapestry receives a render request, it gets an instance of the page, activates it, <em>renders it</em> to HTML, 
	then streams the HTML back to the client.<br/><br/>

	References:	
	<a href="http://people.apache.org/~hlship/t5api/apidocs/org/apache/tapestry5/corelib/components/PageLink.html">PageLink</a>, 
	<a href="http://tapestry.apache.org/page-navigation.html">Page Navigation</a>, 
    <a href="http://tapestry.apache.org/page-navigation.html#PageNavigation-PageRenderRequests">Render Requests</a>, 
	<a href="http://tapestry.apache.org/component-rendering.html">Component Rendering</a>.<br/><br/>

	<t:pagelink t:page="examples/navigation/PageLinks1">Return</t:pagelink><br/><br/>
	
